<DOC><DOCNO> AP890326-0049 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-26-89 1617EST</FILEID><FIRST>d a AM-BRF--ForestPlaneCrash     03-26 0119</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Forest Plane Crash,0120</SECOND><HEAD>Small Plane Crashes In State Forest; Four Killed</HEAD><DATELINE>PITTSFIELD, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A single-engine plane crashed duringrough weather in Pittsfield State Forest, killing all four peopleaboard, authorities said Sunday.   The four-seat Socata TB-10 aircraft, made by the Italian-Frenchconsortium Aerospatiale, was based at Hanscom Field in Bedford. Itwas en route to Albany, N.Y., when it crashed in a light drizzle,according to Federal Aviation Administration spokesman MichaelCiccarelli.   The pilot radioed that he was encountering heavy turbulenceshortly before the plane disappeared from radar late Saturday,authorities said.   State Trooper Christopher Ware said the four victims were allfrom eastern Massachusetts. They were not identified pendingnotification of next of kin.</TEXT></DOC>